                type="document" xml:id="d199">
                <head>199. Editorial Note</head>
                <p>Between March 21 and 24, President <persName corresp="#p_EDD1"
                        >Eisenhower</persName> and Secretary <persName corresp="#p_DJF1"
                        >Dulles</persName> met with British Prime Minister <persName
                        corresp="#p_MHS1">Macmillan</persName> and Foreign Secretary <persName
                        corresp="#p_LS1">Lloyd</persName> at the Mid-Ocean Club in Bermuda and
                    discussed in detail, among other subjects, common problems concerning the Middle
                    East. Documentation recording discussions on the Arab-Israeli dispute, the Suez
                    Canal, and the Gulf of Aqaba is printed in <ref target="frus1955-57v17#pg_448"
                        >volume XVII, pages 448</ref>–<ref target="frus1955-57v17#pg_466">466</ref>.
                    Documentation pertaining to Middle East regional economic and military subjects
                    is printed below. Documentation on all aspects of the preparations for and the
                    proceedings of the Bermuda Conference, including the full texts of <ref
                        target="#d201">Documents 201</ref> and <ref target="#d202">202</ref>, is
                    scheduled for publication in <ref target="frus1955-57v27">volume
                    XXVII</ref>.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
